Three brothers and their nephew died after consuming toxic Muratina brew in Mwaniambogo village, Muranga county. The four were having a house-warming celebration on Saturday after they completed constructing for one of them. County police commander David Kandie said the four complained severe stomach ache. They were rushed to Thika Level Five Hospital where they died. A woman who supplied the brew has been arrested. The wife of the house owner has also been detained by police to assist in investigations. Police have taken the liquor specimen for examination. Click here for the latest political news